'''Euouae''' is a [[mnemonic]] which was used in [[medieval]] [[music]] to denote the sequence of tones in the "seculorum Amen" passage of the hymn ''[[Gloria Patri]]''.  According to the ''[[Guinness Book of World Records]]'', it is the longest word in the [[English language]] which is made up of nothing but [[vowel]]s; it is also the English word with the most consecutive vowels.

